> Well said.
> As an additional FYI:
> Only the pushrods/lifters were choice used. I only mentioned those since
that
> was the topic.
> The bus itself had at least 192,000 miles on it. The reason I say 'at
least' is
> because that is what the odometer showed when I bought the Westy. However,
the
> bus lost 1/10th of a mile for each mile I drove it because of a cracked
gear in
> the speedo. I did not know how long it was that way before I bought it.
> It used a quart of oil every 100 miles. So I pulled the engine and
disassembled
> it. I found no damage to the bottom end. The main and rod journals were
still
> standard, the cam lobes were still like new. I only needed all new
bearings. The
> pistons and cylinders were junk, so I replaced them. I questioned the list
about
> NPR P & C's.... just about everyone pooh-poohed those. Well, I am VERY
happy
> with them also. The heads were fine. No guide wear. All I had to do was
remove
> carbon. The valve seats and valve faces were fine. After lapping them with
fine
> compound, nothing else was needed.
